==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cutin
<hw>Cu"tin</hw> <pr>(k⟦umac⟧"t⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cutis</ets> skin, outside.]</ety> <fld>(Plant Physiol.)</fld>
<def>A waxy substance containing fatty acids, soaps, and resinous
material which, combined with cellulose, forms a substance nearly
impervious to water and constituting the cuticle in plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cutinization</ent>⟦br⟧
